==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Honeydew melon
<hw>Hon"ey*dew` mel"on</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A type of
winter melon (<spn>Cucumis melo</spn> <varn>inodorus</varn>) related to
the muskmelon (<spn>Cucumis melo</spn> <varn>reticulatus</varn>), but
having a smooth pale yellowish-green rind and sweet, juicy, light green
flesh. It is slightly ovoid in shape, commonly about 8 to 10 inches long
on the long axis.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Honeyed</ent>⟦br⟧
